ad.title: Experience babysitters, currently an aupair
ad.content:
My name is Joyce Wambui Mwangi, a 28-year-old au pair currently living in France. I am seeking a new host family, preferably in or around Paris, to continue my journey of cultural exchange and childcare.

For the past six months and finishing my aupair year in August 2025, I have had the privilege of caring for two wonderful boys. This experience has not only enriched my understanding of childcare but also strengthened my adaptability, patience, and creativity in engaging with children. While I do not have a driving license, I am proficient in riding a bike, which I use to run errands or enjoy the outdoors.

I come from a family of five in Kenya, where I am the second-born child. Growing up in a close-knit family has instilled in me a strong sense of responsibility and empathy, qualities I bring to my role as a caregiver.

In addition to my love for children, I am passionate about creative arts and spending time in nature. I enjoy using arts and crafts to engage children in fun and educational activities, and I often encourage outdoor adventures to spark their curiosity and energy.

Although English is my primary language, I am currently learning French to better integrate into life here in France and communicate more effectively with families like yours. I look forward to improving my language skills further with your support.

Thank you for considering me as a potential addition to your family. I am excited about the possibility of building a strong and meaningful bond with you and your children while contributing positively to your household.

I would be happy to discuss my experience and expectations further and answer any questions you may have.
